				<td colspan="2"><span>There is also, though, a difference between declining to post a spoiler and posting a &quot;nyah I know but I won't tell you&quot; sort of taunt.
<br />

<br />
I see the latter fairly frequently on other boards:  &quot;If you can't pass X trial, you're not doing it right.  I won't tell you the strat, except to say you're not doing it right.&quot;  Or &quot;I got X spell to drop last night, but I won't tell you where.&quot;  Etc.
<br />

<br />
I'm not wholly convinced posts like that have much merit.  If you don't want to share information, that's certainly your prerogative.  But I fail to see the purpose of the &quot;I know but won't tell you&quot; post, unless its just chest puffing.  /shrug.</span></td>
